A tornado watch was posted for northeast New York state, much of Vermont and much of New Hampshire. Seven children were killed and 18 injured. A powerful storm system brought strong winds and heavy thunderstorms to the Northeast on Thursday, causing flooding and widespread property damage. , and near blizzard conditions extended over eastern upper Michigan. Seven children died when a wall collapsed in a school cafeteria near Newburgh, NY Tornadoes were reported in New Jersey, Delaware, Virginia and New York, although the National Weather Service was unable to confirm them. A snow squall warning was posted for northeast Ohio. 